<article desc="svg transform support">
   <meta desc="This article presents the support for SVG transform specification" />
   The library support the <code>transform</code> attribute for all elements<note>See 
      <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/SVG11/coords.html#TransformAttribute">The transform attribute</a>
   </note>.
   
   The following transformations are supported:
   <ul>
      <li>
         <code>scale</code>
      </li>      
      <li>
         <code>scaleX</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>scaleY</code>
      </li>      
      <li>
         <code>skewX</code>
      </li>            
      <li>
         <code>skewY</code>
      </li> 
      <li>
         <code>translate</code>
      </li>                          
      <li>
         <code>translateX</code>
      </li>                        
      <li>
         <code>translateY</code>
      </li>                              
      <li>
         <code>rotate</code>
      </li>      
      <li>
         <code>matrix</code>
      </li>                                        
   </ul>
   
   Multiple transformations are allowed in the same <code>transform</code> attribute. For example, this
   declaration is valid:
   <pre syntax="xml">
      &lt;g transform="translate(-10,-20) scale(2) rotate(45) translate(5,10)"&gt;
      &lt;/g&gt;    
   </pre>
            
   <cat id="fromsvgsupport" />
</article>
